OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAll parts will have a dry day
OL,6,Fwith some bright or sunny spells.
OL,7,FNorthern Argyll may see more in the
OL,8,Fway of cloud at times. Warm.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FThis evening will be dry with
OL,11,Fsome late brightness in places. Then
OL,12,Fthe rest of the night will be mainly
OL,13,Fdry although a little drizzle possible
OL,14,Falong the west coast.
OL,15,
OL,16,CThursday:FA dry day on Thursday with
OL,17,Fsome bright or sunny spells developing
OL,18,Fby afternoon but still some cloud
OL,19,Faround. Warm.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
